  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a full kettle</p><p>Bash the <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Remove the <strong>tough outer layer<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> of the lemongrass and set aside, then chop the <strong>softer inner core</strong> roughly</p><p>Peel and roughly chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Slice <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>red chilli</strong> into rounds and roughly chop the <strong>remaining chilli</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610385191693-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610385191693-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610385191693-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610385191693-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1610385191693-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove 2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[4]</span> <strong>outer leaves</strong> from the <strong>spring greens</strong> and add them to a large dish with the <strong>lemongrass</strong> <strong>outer layers</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>rice noodles</strong> and cover with <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Set aside for 12-15 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, drain and set aside</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610385243698-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610385243698-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610385243698-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610385243698-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1610385243698-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>lemongrass </strong>and <strong>chopped red chilli </strong>(save the rounds for garnish!)<strong> </strong>to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>ground turmeric</strong>,<strong> soy sauce, half </strong>the <strong>peanuts </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Blitz to a rough paste – this is your <strong>nutty lemongrass paste</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1610385353858-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1610385353858-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1610385353858-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1610385353858-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1610385353858-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>nutty lemongrass paste</strong>  to the pan and cook for 3-4 mins until fragrant</p><p>Meanwhile, remove the <strong>coconut cream </strong>from the sachet<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> and chop it roughly, then dissolve it in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
